title: F.U. Money: Make As Much Money As You Want And Live Your Life As You Damn Well Please!
author: Dan Lok
review: This is the book that made me realized that time is the most precious and irreplaceable asset that I have. I would very much say that I wouldn't be where I am today without reading this book. The author is a bit controversial, but I personally think the content of this particular book is good. I would highly recommend this book if you can excuse his use of profanity and harsh words.

title: Awaken the Giant Within: How to Take Immediate Control of Your Mental, Emotional, Physical and Financial Destiny!
author: Tony Robbins
review: I was going to read his first book 'Unlimited Power' first. However, this one was available in the library first, so this was the first book that I've read from Tony Robbins. 10 out of 10 recommend this. The major takeaway from this book for me was finding a role model. Someone, somwhere, must have done the things that you've been dreaming to achieve. You first need to know what it is that you want, know it is possible to achieve with inspiration from someone that's done it, and mirror and execute it!

title: What To Say When You Talk To Your Self
author: Shad Helmstetter
review: I thought this was going to be another book with a catchy title. I mean, who doesn't know what to say to yourself? The content is surprisingly eye-opening for me. It talks about the five levels of self-talk and how self-talk can help you become your only long-term motivator. Two stars deducted because some of his negative self-talk examples don't make sense and I don't like his overuse of computer analogy in the book.

title: The 10X Rule: The Only Difference Between Success and Failure
author: Grant Cardone
review: This book inspired me to "Level UP" myself. The book itself was valuable to me, but the author is not a great influencer in my opinion. He might be a great property saleman, but I don't agree with the way he took money from his followers. The book itself though, definitely brings value to me as a person.
